State Name: Figures represent the percentage of each state's nonagricultural wage and salary employees who are union members.
Estimates are based on the 1983-2015 Current Population Survey (CPS) Outgoing Rotation Group (ORG) earnings files and
the 1977-81 May CPS earnings files.  Details on data and methodology are provided in the text.
Use of these data requires citation.
Barry T. Hirsch, David A. Macpherson, and Wayne G. Vroman, “Estimates of Union Density by State,” Monthly Labor Review, Vol. 124, No. 7, July 2001, pp. 51-55.
